Hi, my name is Meatball! I'm a 16yr old handsome gentleman looking for my forever home!I am very sweet, friendly and affectionate! Neck and shoulder massages are my favorites, but I also enjoy having my back and tail petted. I might take a little gentle coaxing to get me out of my cubby, but once I'm out, I love to be held and will stay calm and relaxed in your arms, whether sitting or walking around. I will purr when happy and look at you with a loving gaze.I am FIV+ and so will need to be indoor only, and either an only kitty or live with other FIV+ kitties. I am healthy right now and ready for my forever home! Yes, 16yrs old, FIV+ and healthy! Did you know that FIV+ kitties can live just as long as other kitties? The officers and veterinarians at the shelter will be happy to answer any questions you may have.I am litter box trained, neutered, current on my vaccinations, and micro chipped!If you would like to meet me in purr-son, you can find me at the King County Pet Adoption Center in Kent, located at 21615 64th Ave S. I can't wait to see you! We just might make the purr-fect family!When you do come for a visit, make sure to reference my ID #A480023. See you soon!

Hi, my name is Bella!  I'm a 13yr old sweet girl waiting for my forever home!Let my gorgeous eyes captivate you!  I am very friendly and affectionate.  While not keen on being held, I love to be petted, especially gentle head scratches and the "double cheek smoosh".  What is that you ask?  Well, it's where you scratch both my cheeks at the same time!  I will purr and pace in appreciation!  I even like gentle hugs.I do have kidney disease and spinal osteoarthritis, but am very sweet and gentle and ready for my forever home.  Due to my age and special needs, I would do best in an adult only home, so they will know to be as gentle with me as I am with them.I am litter box trained, spayed, current on vaccinations, and micro chipped!If you would like to meet me in purr-son and get to know me better, you can find me at the King County Pet Adoption Center in Kent, located at 21615 64th Ave S.  Please come and see me today...I can't wait to meet you!  We just might make the purr-fect family!When you do come for a visit, please make sure to reference my ID #A466115.  See you soon!

I do have a urinary condition that is well-controlled by giving me a special diet - both dry and canned food. I may seem a little shy when you meet me due to all of the changes in my life, but once you start to pet me I'll be your faithful friend forever.
